<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :brickwall --><img src=http://members.cox.net/skoriksis/smilies/brickwall.gif ALT=":brickwall"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I never claimed we should resort to anarchy, or that a lack of government was cool. <br>
I asked why spend so much money on weapons that countries &quot;never planned to use&quot; when the money could be used for more important stuff like the health and education of it's people. Then in my second post I asked how you could think that the governments of the world were doing a good job and I really believe that if you took the time to find out what your government spends its money on you'd be pissed off. That's your hard earned tax dollar that they're wasting on fucking $35,000 dining tables that are going to be replaced as soon as you get a new Prime Minister (or President in your case) whos wife wants to redecorate. Just as that $35,000 would have been better spent at my local primary school so too would the hundreds of thousands of dollars my government spends on planting fucking trees UNDER overhanging power lines, pay council gardeners to care for them, pay water tanker companies to come out twice a week in summer and water the saplings which would die in our heat without water, only to have to spend  more money  to cut the fucking branches off a few years later as they've now grown too big and are starting to interfere with the power lines they were PLANTED UNDER. How is it wrong to wonder if maybe all the money they're spending on the military and &quot;weapons of mass destruction&quot; is maybe a bit over the top, and couldn't we just spend 10% less in this area and reallocate that money to a department that needs it?<br>
Does anyone still really think their government's doing a great job with no need for improvement?<br>
But, how the fuck does thinking your government spends its money on shit equate to anarchy?<br>
