<br>
Anarchism: &quot;political theory opposed to all forms of government. Anarchists believe that the highest attainment of humanity is the freedom of the individual to express himself, unhindered by any form of repression or control from without. The belief that all governments rest on violence to control their subjects&quot;<br>
<br>
Ok.  So let's look at that.  That last sentence, while it may be true in some places/situations, keeps order.  It allows for those who are not breaking laws to live in harmony.  That's how I am.  I don't break the law, I don't have a problem with it.  I express myself just fine.  And the way &quot;express&quot; is used in that definition leaves a bad taste in my mouth.  What if the way someone wants to &quot;express&quot; themselves is by blowing up a couple hundred people in his own community.  There will be no retribution for it since there is no government.  I suppose you could argue the people of the community will go after said bomber, but how will they even get to him without him blowing them up first?  Well they need weapons.  Then suddenly you got yourself a government.  A group of people using violence to control a subject that decided to express himself by blowing up a hundred people.   <br>
<br>
I suppose you could argue no one would do that because they're more advanced than that.  Heh.  One thing I've learned is that sometimes, crazy people are just born.  I have a 2nd cousin who has a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">slight</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> chemical imbalance.  My family and I were staying in their house as guests and I accidentally left a popcorn bowl in the sink.  The FIRST TIME I had ever done it.  Well this bitch waltzes in and goes batshit, screaming, stomping.  It was like she was possessed.  Then she stormed out, called my mom a bitch because of something I did, and less than a week later we moved out.  Chemical imbalance.  Bitch would get angry very easily over little shit.  Sometimes, crazy people are just born.  Sometimes, people just turn greedy.  Anarchy can VERY EASILY become a dictatorship.  Ruled by fear and violence.  Anarchy itself isn't violence based and seems like a good idea, but it can easily turn into a government that is.  Just be thankful that wherever you are, you have the freedom to play video games and post on message boards and be happy. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113883">Landale Palemoon (Primary Gear, WITH NEW AND IMPROVED PANTS!)</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
